  stable 1.0.1 1.0.0
  CATEGORY='graphic'
 ATTRIBUTE='library'
    SOURCE="ilmbase-$VERSION.tar.gz"
       URL='http://savannah.nongnu.org/download/openexr/'
  HOMEPAGE='http://www.openexr.com'
      OPTS='--enable-static=no'
  ESTIMATE='500'
      DESC='ilmbase provides libraries that openexr uses.

IlmThread is a thread abstraction library for
use with OpenEXR and other software packages.
It currently supports pthreads and Windows threads.

Imath implements 2D and 3D vectors, 3x3 and 4x4 matrices,
quaternions and other useful 2D and 3D math functions.

Iex is an exception-handling library.'

build(){
 case $VERSION in
  1.0.1) rm -f /usr/lib{,64}/libImath.so ;;
 esac
 default_build
}

current(){
 case $VERSION in
  1.0.1) [ -f /usr/lib/libImath.so ] ||
         [ -f /usr/lib64/libImath.so ] ;;
 esac
}
